race.comment: RAPBIDASH (6) joins a long list of gallopers enjoying success since a recent switch to the Bjorn Baker yard. Opened with a placing in heavy going at Canterbury then raced handy and pulled out too many stops against the mares over 1300m at Rosehill last start. Takes on the boys today and draws out wide but she can get the job done again. JACOB'S LADDER (7) is looking for this trip now after three runs back. Races well here with two minor placings from as many appearances, including one over today's journey. Looks a nice chance from an inside gate with Zac Lloyd back aboard. The interesting runner is SUPER MIRAGE (10) who hasn't appeared since winning on debut in the UK 13 months ago. Now with Waller and has been gelded. Watch the betting. ROTAGILLA (2) returns from a four-month spell. Improved as the last prep progressed. Two recent trials should have him ready to run well. KILMAN (14) has done little in two runs this campaign but is lightly raced and can improve.
